      "description": "value - Up is defined as an increase in values of the input channels, and down is a decrease in values of the inputs. amp - Up is defined as an increase in amplitude (moving away from zero) and down is defined as a decrease in amplitude (moving towards zero) of each input channel. mag - All the input channels are treated as components of one vector, and each operation is applied to the vector as a whole. Only the first parameter in Lag, Overshoot, Clamp Slope and Clamp Acceleration applies in this mode. rotation - Allows the lag to work with quaternion rotations.",
